@article{bagnuls85,
abstract = {The theoretical framework and the details of calculations of nonasymptotic critical behavior, above Tc, previously published for n=1, are presented and extended to the cases n=2 and 3. The complete description of the real preasymptotic critical domain Dpreas needs only three adjustable parameters. We show that the 4 model at infinite cutoff is sufficient to obtain this description. The higher-transient and finite-cutoff effects in Dpreas affect only the adjustable parameters. A precise nonperturbative treatment of the 4 field theory exactly for d=3, in the spirit of the Parisi work, yields nonasymptotic functions of temperature which, including all the quantitative universal characteristics of the critical behavior in Dpreas, are adapted to a suitable comparison with experiments. We emphasize that this work allows a determination, within the experimental accuracy, of the size of Dpreas and an appreciation of the effects of the higher corrections to scaling. We also give the estimates for n=1, 2, and 3 of a new universal combination of amplitudes (RBcr) which concerns the specific heat alone. {\textcopyright} 1985 The American Physical Society.},
